summary:
The Security Council,

Adopting resolution 1993 (2011) at its 6571st meeting on 29 June 2011,

Recalling previous resolutions on the International Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia (ICTY), particularly 827 (1993), 1503 (2003), 1534 (2004), and 1966 (2010),

Noting the ICTY's Completion Strategy Report and the need to expeditiously complete its remaining work by 31 December 2014,

Decides to:

1. Extend the terms of office of 8 permanent judges and 9 ad litem judges at the ICTY until 31 December 2012 or until completion of assigned cases, if sooner;

2. Reaffirm the necessity of trials for indicted persons, particularly Goran Hadzic, and calls on States, especially those of the former Yugoslavia, to intensify cooperation and assistance;

3. Stress the importance of adequate staffing for the ICTY to complete its work expeditiously and call on relevant UN bodies to find practicable solutions;

4. Commend States that have concluded agreements for enforcement of sentences and call on States to renew their commitment to enforcement;

5. Call on States that have not concluded agreements to consider doing so;

6. Decide to remain seized of the matter.
